ed module. When I reset modules in `afterEach`, the next test's dynamic import should get a fresh module, but I need to verify that the mock from `vi.mock()` at the top level will still apply to that reimported module—and based on vitest's behavior, it should since mocks are hoisted and persist across resets.\n\nThe key insight is that my `mockCreateClient` function is defined in the outer scope, so even when the mock factory is called again after a reset, it references the same function object, which means call tracking should work correctly. However, for the singleton pattern test, I need to think through whether resetting modules actually breaks the singleton behavior as intended. version, `createClient` isn't called again, so `a === b` checks out and `mockCreateClient` is called exactly once. The `mockClear()` in `afterEach` resets the call count between tests while keeping the mock intact, which is what I need.\n\nNow I'm ready to write the actual test and implementation files. Let me verify the config field name first—checking the package docs confirms `password` is the correct option name. I'll set up the directory structure and create the necessary files.\n\nWriting test and implementation files...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3200,"cache_read_input_tokens":43752,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3200},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8b451bd-f0f7-46fe-b150-5d64a0bdd171","uuid":"8384a5a8-d4b9-44ba-b35c-7be3d178cb77"}
